1
00:00:00,410 --> 00:00:01,410
Quiet.

2
00:00:02,110 --> 00:00:04,810
Professor, I had no choice.

3
00:00:05,010 --> 00:00:07,280
Father suspects us.

4
00:00:08,480 --> 00:00:10,280
Are you bringing up their marriage...

5
00:00:10,280 --> 00:00:12,950
just because you're afraid
we'll get caught?

6
00:00:14,090 --> 00:00:17,820
This is an absurd solution.
That marriage is out of the question.

7
00:00:18,720 --> 00:00:20,360
It was because of us.

8
00:00:20,360 --> 00:00:23,700
So even after the car accident,
to keep you out of it,

9
00:00:23,800 --> 00:00:25,930
I covered for you the best I could.

10
00:00:30,140 --> 00:00:31,170
What?

11
00:00:31,600 --> 00:00:36,040
So that means Chae Hwa Young
was involved in my dad's accident.

12
00:00:37,110 --> 00:00:38,310
I knew it.

13
00:00:38,640 --> 00:00:41,580
Hwa Young, I'm not blaming you,

14
00:00:41,880 --> 00:00:45,980
but I drove all the way out there
that night just to see you.

15
00:00:46,220 --> 00:00:49,990
- I was willing to risk it all.
- Protected me? What do you mean by that?

16
00:00:50,560 --> 00:00:53,890
I'm a little hurt you'd say that,
Professor.

17
00:00:53,890 --> 00:00:57,230
I'm hurt too.
It's because I love you, Hwa Young.

18
00:00:57,230 --> 00:00:58,500
Let's be honest, Professor.

19
00:00:58,760 --> 00:01:02,230
You won't divorce Lawyer Han for me.

20
00:01:02,900 --> 00:01:04,200
What are you talking about?

21
00:01:05,100 --> 00:01:07,940
If I divorced her and proposed to you,
would you say yes?

22
00:01:11,710 --> 00:01:12,780
See?

23
00:01:14,180 --> 00:01:15,180
Anyway,

24
00:01:15,710 --> 00:01:18,450
Jun Ho and Director Ma's marriage
is out of the question.

25
00:01:18,650 --> 00:01:23,190
My daughter loves General Manager Kang.
They've loved each other longer than us.

26
00:01:23,290 --> 00:01:25,460
As a mother, how can I stand in the way
of my daughter's love?

27
00:01:25,760 --> 00:01:27,160
I could never do that.

28
00:01:27,330 --> 00:01:29,390
Hwa Young, this is wrong.

29
00:01:29,390 --> 00:01:32,000
To be in-laws
and pretend we were never lovers,

30
00:01:32,060 --> 00:01:34,100
that alone would be absurd.

31
00:01:34,370 --> 00:01:35,870
But will you do it knowingly?

32
00:01:36,800 --> 00:01:38,170
I'm completely against it.

33
00:01:38,700 --> 00:01:39,700
So then,

34
00:01:40,370 --> 00:01:42,840
Baek Ho's older brother
is General Manager Kang Jun Ho?

35
00:01:45,580 --> 00:01:46,880
I can't believe they're brothers.

36
00:01:49,010 --> 00:01:51,750
CEO Chae is being arrogant.

37
00:01:52,220 --> 00:01:54,090
After all, marriage
is one of life’s biggest events.

38
00:01:54,390 --> 00:01:56,820
How could she decide
something like that on her own...

39
00:01:56,990 --> 00:01:59,820
without even consulting you, darling?

40
00:01:59,960 --> 00:02:02,460
Just because CEO Chae decided it
doesn't make it a done deal!

41
00:02:02,730 --> 00:02:03,960
So, darling,

42
00:02:04,130 --> 00:02:07,830
do you object to Seo Rin
marrying Professor Kang’s son?

43
00:02:07,930 --> 00:02:10,400
Of course I do! Not a chance!

44
00:02:11,200 --> 00:02:14,010
How could we let our Seo Rin marry
into a family like that?

45
00:02:14,440 --> 00:02:18,810
But from what I've seen,
Chef Kang Jun Ho is tall and handsome.

46
00:02:21,110 --> 00:02:24,450
Our Seo Rin was crazy about
Kang Jun Ho for a while,

47
00:02:24,720 --> 00:02:26,820
but thankfully, she seems to
have calmed down about it now.

48
00:02:27,490 --> 00:02:29,120
It's best to just leave her alone.

49
00:02:29,790 --> 00:02:33,390
- Opposing it now would fan the flames.
- That's true.

50
00:02:33,460 --> 00:02:37,360
You know how people are.
Tell them no, and they want to do it more.

51
00:02:38,530 --> 00:02:40,530
By the way, Professor Kang
went to the restroom.

52
00:02:40,530 --> 00:02:41,530
What's taking him so long?

53
00:02:41,970 --> 00:02:44,970
Professor, let's talk about this later.

54
00:02:45,340 --> 00:02:47,070
If my family overhears us,

55
00:02:47,440 --> 00:02:50,140
- it'll be trouble for us.
- All right.

56
00:02:50,480 --> 00:02:53,210
- I'll call you tomorrow.
- Wait, Professor.

57
00:02:54,610 --> 00:02:56,850
Please, try to understand.

58
00:02:57,720 --> 00:02:59,950
Anyway, this isn't just about me.

59
00:03:00,020 --> 00:03:04,160
I don't think Jun Ho wants
to marry Director Ma either.

60
00:03:04,320 --> 00:03:05,360
So...

61
00:03:06,220 --> 00:03:07,230
you can understand it that way.

62
00:03:08,390 --> 00:03:10,330
Why are you so dead set against this?

63
00:03:10,760 --> 00:03:13,500
This is Jun Ho's chance to marry
into the Dream Group family.

64
00:03:13,500 --> 00:03:15,630
How do you not know that?

65
00:03:15,630 --> 00:03:20,140
Of course I'm against it!
If this happens, what about us?

66
00:03:20,170 --> 00:03:21,970
Our relationship would be over for good.

67
00:03:24,410 --> 00:03:25,410
Professor...

68
00:03:36,890 --> 00:03:39,190
If Seo Rin marries Jun Ho...

69
00:03:40,490 --> 00:03:41,760
Hold on.

70
00:03:41,760 --> 00:03:43,660
How would we all be related then?

71
00:03:44,360 --> 00:03:47,400
That means Seo Rin
could become my sister-in-law.

72
00:03:52,200 --> 00:03:55,340
Ma’am, are you in there?
The chairman is asking for you.

73
00:03:57,780 --> 00:03:59,010
Just a second.

74
00:04:05,120 --> 00:04:08,450
I had to take a call.
I was just on my way down.

75
00:04:08,650 --> 00:04:10,190
You said Father was looking for me?

76
00:04:10,360 --> 00:04:12,320
The Professor went to the restroom
and hasn't come back yet.

77
00:04:12,820 --> 00:04:14,160
Okay, let's go down.

78
00:04:23,800 --> 00:04:25,670
I saw Professor Kang a moment ago.

79
00:04:25,940 --> 00:04:28,910
He seemed to be on a long call
with Lawyer Han.

80
00:04:29,740 --> 00:04:33,480
I guess they were discussing
General Manager Kang's marriage.

81
00:04:33,710 --> 00:04:36,010
We were wondering
what was taking him so long.

82
00:04:36,710 --> 00:04:38,080
Here he comes now.

83
00:04:38,950 --> 00:04:42,790
Professor Kang, it seems your call
with Lawyer Han ran long.

84
00:04:43,320 --> 00:04:44,390
Well...

85
00:04:44,690 --> 00:04:45,690
Yes.

86
00:04:52,100 --> 00:04:54,970
How my dad was hit and killed
by Professor Kang's car...

87
00:04:55,700 --> 00:04:57,640
It's all finally starting
to fall into place.

88
00:04:58,170 --> 00:05:00,870
- Why you did that to Suk Hee...
- Chae Hwa Young, Manager Lee,

89
00:05:01,310 --> 00:05:04,540
and Ssangkal must've harmed my dad
at that hotel.

90
00:05:05,910 --> 00:05:07,610
Afterward, they moved him
to the scene of the accident,

91
00:05:08,480 --> 00:05:10,180
and Chae Hwa Young
lured Professor Kang there...

92
00:05:10,480 --> 00:05:13,020
to frame him for a staged car accident.

93
00:05:17,720 --> 00:05:19,360
Chae Hwa Young is not even human.

94
00:05:20,190 --> 00:05:23,630
How could she frame the man
she was having an affair with?

95
00:05:26,530 --> 00:05:28,730
But it's all just circumstantial evidence.
It's useless.

96
00:05:29,600 --> 00:05:32,800
I have to find conclusive proof.

97
00:05:38,780 --> 00:05:41,580
So, why did Dad go to Chairman Ma's house?

98
00:05:42,510 --> 00:05:46,880
I'm sure it was about your marriage,
Jun Ho.

99
00:05:47,090 --> 00:05:50,460
What about you, Jun Ho? Do you want
to marry Chairman Ma's granddaughter?

100
00:05:50,920 --> 00:05:53,930
Director Ma looks an awful lot
like Jang Mi.

101
00:05:54,260 --> 00:05:57,200
Do you have to compare everyone
to Oh Jang Mi?

102
00:05:57,500 --> 00:06:01,830
You're just so blinded by love.

103
00:06:02,230 --> 00:06:03,770
Speaking of which, Jun Ho,

104
00:06:04,670 --> 00:06:07,870
- what do you really think about it?
- I'm not interested.

105
00:06:08,510 --> 00:06:12,040
I don't get why CEO Chae is so pushy,

106
00:06:12,610 --> 00:06:14,880
but marriage is
about the two people involved, isn't it?

107
00:06:15,010 --> 00:06:18,320
- So you're not into Director Ma?
- I don't know.

108
00:06:19,180 --> 00:06:21,750
At first, Director Ma
was the one pursuing me,

109
00:06:22,320 --> 00:06:24,060
but now it feels like she's avoiding me.

110
00:06:24,690 --> 00:06:26,390
Maybe because of the lingering effects
from her car accident,

111
00:06:26,720 --> 00:06:28,690
it looks like her personality
has completely changed.

112
00:06:28,730 --> 00:06:30,660
The accident
must have really taken a toll on her.

113
00:06:31,530 --> 00:06:35,930
In any case, I'm all for you marrying
into Chairman Ma's family.

114
00:06:36,070 --> 00:06:37,740
I've got no problem with it.

115
00:06:38,100 --> 00:06:41,610
- As long as she's not a complete brat.
- We haven't even been on a single date,

116
00:06:42,040 --> 00:06:43,370
so what's all this talk about marriage?

117
00:06:57,220 --> 00:07:00,060
The person you're calling is unavailable.
Connecting to voicemail.

118
00:07:05,230 --> 00:07:07,900
I was able to call you
whenever I wanted, Jang Mi.

119
00:07:09,300 --> 00:07:10,330
And when I missed you,

120
00:07:11,140 --> 00:07:13,000
I was able to rush over and see you.

121
00:07:14,470 --> 00:07:16,240
I miss those times, Jang Mi.

122
00:07:18,210 --> 00:07:20,710
Please, wake up now, Jang Mi.

123
00:07:26,720 --> 00:07:29,720
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

124
00:07:34,290 --> 00:07:35,730
In the car accident case,

125
00:07:36,160 --> 00:07:39,530
Professor Kang Nam Bong deliberately left
Chae Hwa Young out of his statement.

126
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:41,330
He was completely under her spell.

127
00:07:45,740 --> 00:07:46,740
Mom.

128
00:07:47,410 --> 00:07:48,440
My dear mom.

129
00:07:49,240 --> 00:07:51,640
You have to be strong
and take care of yourself without me.

130
00:07:52,340 --> 00:07:53,340
Okay?

131
00:07:54,310 --> 00:07:55,310
Tae Pyung.

132
00:07:55,910 --> 00:07:57,280
Just wait a little longer.

133
00:07:58,180 --> 00:08:00,380
I swear I will drag Chae Hwa Young here...

134
00:08:00,920 --> 00:08:02,820
and make her get on her knees
and beg for forgiveness.

135
00:08:03,690 --> 00:08:06,120
Chae Hwa Young, I will never forgive you.

136
00:08:06,790 --> 00:08:08,660
For causing my father's death.

137
00:08:08,660 --> 00:08:10,800
For toying with Tae Pyung's dreams.

138
00:08:11,930 --> 00:08:13,830
For ruining my mother's life.

139
00:08:14,970 --> 00:08:17,670
For kidnapping Seo Rin and using her
for your own greedy ambitions.

140
00:08:17,740 --> 00:08:20,670
I will make you pay for every last thing
you've done.

141
00:08:21,670 --> 00:08:22,670
I swear it.

142
00:08:47,630 --> 00:08:48,630
Aren't you getting in?

143
00:08:55,570 --> 00:08:56,870
Doors closing.

144
00:09:02,210 --> 00:09:03,210
Director Ma.

145
00:09:03,880 --> 00:09:06,350
- Your personality's changed quite a bit.
- What?

146
00:09:06,650 --> 00:09:07,820
Me?

147
00:09:07,890 --> 00:09:10,420
You're completely different
from the Director Ma I used to know.

148
00:09:10,990 --> 00:09:13,260
Not that I mind the change.

149
00:09:14,190 --> 00:09:15,830
Are you saying you like it?

150
00:09:17,430 --> 00:09:18,700
I didn't say I like it.

151
00:09:21,730 --> 00:09:25,500
How did I used to treat you,
General Manager Kang?

152
00:09:26,940 --> 00:09:31,380
(General Manager Kang Jun Ho)

153
00:09:33,140 --> 00:09:34,150
You really...

154
00:09:34,680 --> 00:09:36,510
don't remember at all?

155
00:09:36,910 --> 00:09:37,920
Pardon?

156
00:09:38,950 --> 00:09:41,050
I'm sorry.

157
00:09:42,420 --> 00:09:43,550
In a nutshell,

158
00:09:44,390 --> 00:09:45,820
you were my stalker.

159
00:09:46,420 --> 00:09:47,890
What? A stalker?

160
00:09:48,030 --> 00:09:51,900
I'm sure you just thought you were
expressing your interest in me.

161
00:09:52,760 --> 00:09:55,370
- That must have been awful.
- It was extremely unpleasant.

162
00:09:55,900 --> 00:09:58,940
Still, that's taking it too far.
How could he call Seo Rin a stalker?

163
00:10:00,640 --> 00:10:03,570
If I offended you, I sincerely apologize.

164
00:10:04,810 --> 00:10:07,550
Getting an apology from you, Director Ma…

165
00:10:08,280 --> 00:10:11,050
- I never expected this side of you.
- Don't worry.

166
00:10:11,520 --> 00:10:15,190
I'll stay out of your way
unless it's about work.

167
00:10:24,260 --> 00:10:25,260
What was that?

168
00:10:26,660 --> 00:10:28,930
Why do I feel like I'm the one
who just got rejected?

169
00:10:30,330 --> 00:10:31,970
What did you find out
about what I asked you?

170
00:10:32,370 --> 00:10:33,940
Was it Jin Hong Ju's doing?

171
00:10:34,770 --> 00:10:38,680
Yes. The flower shop still had the number
that placed the order, so I checked it.

172
00:10:39,340 --> 00:10:41,450
And it matched her number.

173
00:10:42,850 --> 00:10:44,780
So she ordered the flowers herself...

174
00:10:45,180 --> 00:10:47,550
and then had the gall to make it seem like
someone sent the flowers?

175
00:10:47,820 --> 00:10:50,990
If that's the case, the person
who left the note on your desk before...

176
00:10:51,060 --> 00:10:53,560
Exactly. It had to be Jin Hong Ju.

177
00:10:54,790 --> 00:10:58,700
Someone who can freely access my office
and knows about me and Professor Kang...

178
00:10:58,760 --> 00:11:00,200
Who else could it be besides
that Jin Hong Ju and her mother?

179
00:11:00,660 --> 00:11:02,170
What are you going to do about it?

180
00:11:02,870 --> 00:11:06,300
I'll have to teach her a lesson about
what happens when she messes with me.

181
00:11:06,970 --> 00:11:09,740
That will make sure she never dreams
of pulling a stunt like that again.

182
00:11:12,640 --> 00:11:14,310
Baek Ho, are you free today?

183
00:11:14,680 --> 00:11:17,520
I have something to talk about.
Meet me at a bar tonight.

184
00:11:17,850 --> 00:11:20,120
It's time for you to repay
the favor you owe me.

185
00:11:23,320 --> 00:11:24,320
Team Leader Jin.

186
00:11:25,260 --> 00:11:27,120
- What?
- Aren't you spending...

187
00:11:27,120 --> 00:11:28,590
a little too much time
on your phone during work hours?

188
00:11:28,860 --> 00:11:31,100
What message are you waiting for
so desperately?

189
00:11:31,460 --> 00:11:33,430
I'm coordinating with the agency.

190
00:11:33,860 --> 00:11:36,300
It's regarding the press release
for the hotel's new season.

191
00:11:36,500 --> 00:11:40,570
That article was released an hour ago.
Didn't you check it?

192
00:11:41,770 --> 00:11:43,610
Are you working or just slacking off?

193
00:11:44,080 --> 00:11:46,210
When did Ma Seo Rin become so meticulous?

194
00:11:46,540 --> 00:11:49,250
I still haven't received the email
with the link and reports.

195
00:11:49,310 --> 00:11:51,250
I can tell you're slacking off.

196
00:11:51,650 --> 00:11:53,820
During work hours,
focus only on your work.

197
00:11:55,190 --> 00:11:56,190
Yes.

198
00:12:07,100 --> 00:12:08,970
I guess we went through all that
for our luck to finally turn.

199
00:12:09,600 --> 00:12:12,570
Jang Mi's hospital bills were so high.
I can finally breathe a little.

200
00:12:12,770 --> 00:12:16,140
After the order from the orphanage,
word of mouth spread like wildfire.

201
00:12:16,210 --> 00:12:18,480
And now tons of people are asking
for our packed lunches.

202
00:12:18,540 --> 00:12:20,740
Our sales have practically quintupled.

203
00:12:21,380 --> 00:12:22,850
When did you say you were opening a store?

204
00:12:22,850 --> 00:12:25,150
As soon as I finish my training.

205
00:12:25,250 --> 00:12:28,450
Mom, does this mean we'll be rich now?
Are we making lots of money?

206
00:12:28,650 --> 00:12:33,320
You have to work hard to get rich.
Bo Ra, you need to listen to Mommy,

207
00:12:33,390 --> 00:12:35,760
and do well in preschool.
That's how you'll get rich.

208
00:12:36,030 --> 00:12:38,460
- Really, Uncle?
- That's right.

209
00:12:39,030 --> 00:12:41,070
- Tae Pyung.
- Yes.

210
00:12:41,130 --> 00:12:44,840
Suk Hee made japchae, and It's delicious.

211
00:12:45,340 --> 00:12:48,110
Grandma, we're going to be rich!

212
00:12:48,470 --> 00:12:49,910
Being rich sounds great.

213
00:12:50,470 --> 00:12:51,680
Suk Hee is so happy!

214
00:12:51,680 --> 00:12:54,850
I'm so happy
I can eat lots of delicious things.

215
00:12:55,210 --> 00:12:59,120
- I'm excited too!
- Yas, It's so exciting!

216
00:13:00,220 --> 00:13:01,220
It's wonderful, isn't it?

217
00:13:10,430 --> 00:13:12,330
You understand
what I need you to do, right?

218
00:13:12,700 --> 00:13:14,830
- Yes.
- Make sure...

219
00:13:15,230 --> 00:13:16,470
you have to call this number.

220
00:13:16,800 --> 00:13:17,900
I know.

221
00:13:20,940 --> 00:13:23,310
Why is time going by so slowly?

222
00:13:24,180 --> 00:13:26,340
(Lawyer Kang Baek Ho)

223
00:13:28,380 --> 00:13:29,710
(Jin Hong Ju)

224
00:13:41,230 --> 00:13:42,860
This is a bar in Hangang-dong.

225
00:13:43,090 --> 00:13:46,030
The owner of this phone
is completely passed out drunk.

226
00:13:46,830 --> 00:13:48,800
I called you
because you were on her recent calls list.

227
00:13:49,130 --> 00:13:50,200
Could you please come pick her up?

228
00:13:54,210 --> 00:13:55,770
Okay, please text me the address.

229
00:13:57,170 --> 00:13:58,840
Thank you. I'll make it worth your while.

230
00:14:19,000 --> 00:14:20,160
How's this?

231
00:14:20,160 --> 00:14:22,900
- Do you think this is a good position?
- Looks good.

232
00:14:23,600 --> 00:14:24,940
I'm really rooting for you.

233
00:14:31,040 --> 00:14:32,440
I heard from my mother.

234
00:14:33,980 --> 00:14:35,780
About me and Director Ma Seo Rin
getting married.

235
00:14:38,420 --> 00:14:40,080
Lawyer Han told me...

236
00:14:40,380 --> 00:14:42,320
that we should go along with your choice.

237
00:14:42,320 --> 00:14:43,420
Ma'am.

238
00:14:44,260 --> 00:14:46,890
I don't believe
in marrying for love alone either.

239
00:14:47,960 --> 00:14:48,960
But still,

240
00:14:49,990 --> 00:14:53,000
a marriage should be built
on affection and trust...

241
00:14:53,060 --> 00:14:54,770
Affection and trust. Sure, those are nice.

242
00:14:55,530 --> 00:14:58,070
It's not like I don't know your family.

243
00:14:58,070 --> 00:15:00,140
You know me, Seo Rin,

244
00:15:00,470 --> 00:15:02,740
and even Chairman Ma quite well.

245
00:15:03,210 --> 00:15:05,410
So what more trust is there to build?

246
00:15:06,810 --> 00:15:09,710
Don't drag your feet.
You'll ruin a good thing.

247
00:15:12,250 --> 00:15:14,590
Or is Seo Rin simply
not good enough for you?

248
00:15:15,420 --> 00:15:17,990
She's not good enough for you to refuse
to be a son-in-law of a rich family?

249
00:15:17,990 --> 00:15:19,490
As I've told you before,

250
00:15:20,420 --> 00:15:21,430
A tycoon family?

251
00:15:22,060 --> 00:15:24,800
- That kind of thing means nothing to me.
- "That kind of thing?"

252
00:15:27,460 --> 00:15:29,500
In that case, I'm truly disappointed.

253
00:15:32,470 --> 00:15:33,470
If...

254
00:15:35,270 --> 00:15:39,040
I weren't the biological son
of Kang Nam Bong and Han Young Ja,

255
00:15:40,380 --> 00:15:42,080
would you still want me
as your son-in-law?

256
00:15:50,550 --> 00:15:53,690
(General Manager Kang Jun Ho)

257
00:15:53,760 --> 00:15:57,060
(Younger Brother)

258
00:16:03,270 --> 00:16:05,400
Why isn't Jun Ho picking up?

259
00:16:09,510 --> 00:16:10,740
I was adopted.

260
00:16:13,040 --> 00:16:14,850
I'm telling you this because
I'm sure a CEO of your stature...

261
00:16:15,710 --> 00:16:18,720
wouldn't accept a man who was adopted
into a family as a son-in-law.

262
00:16:19,820 --> 00:16:20,820
Now, if you'll excuse me.

263
00:16:21,920 --> 00:16:22,920
I know.

264
00:16:26,590 --> 00:16:28,730
So sit down.

265
00:16:34,700 --> 00:16:35,700
You know?

266
00:16:36,300 --> 00:16:40,240
Don't tell me you ran a background check
on me through some business network?

267
00:16:40,400 --> 00:16:41,870
Professor Kang told me.

268
00:16:43,040 --> 00:16:44,540
Don't get me wrong.

269
00:16:45,240 --> 00:16:48,750
We happened to be talking about you,
and I'm the one who pried.

270
00:16:49,050 --> 00:16:50,150
Then...

271
00:16:51,780 --> 00:16:53,620
even knowing that I'm adopted,

272
00:16:54,790 --> 00:16:58,120
- you still want me as your son-in-law?
- I already told you.

273
00:16:58,660 --> 00:17:00,420
I couldn't be more serious.

274
00:17:01,260 --> 00:17:02,730
As a husband for my Seo Rin,

275
00:17:03,430 --> 00:17:05,760
there's no one more perfect than you.

276
00:17:09,300 --> 00:17:10,300
General Manager Kang.

277
00:17:11,800 --> 00:17:13,040
Help me out here.

278
00:17:13,840 --> 00:17:14,840
Please?

279
00:17:28,990 --> 00:17:30,490
Hi, son.

280
00:17:30,890 --> 00:17:32,720
Hey Mom, you sound happy.

281
00:17:33,760 --> 00:17:34,860
Of course, I am.

282
00:17:35,430 --> 00:17:39,700
I won my case today,
so your dad and I are celebrating.

283
00:17:40,300 --> 00:17:42,300
Is Jun Ho home? Put him on.

284
00:17:42,370 --> 00:17:45,840
He's probably still at work.
Try calling him there.

285
00:17:45,900 --> 00:17:47,370
I have, but he's not picking up.

286
00:17:47,600 --> 00:17:49,110
Why do you need him?

287
00:17:50,170 --> 00:17:51,340
Never mind.

288
00:17:51,340 --> 00:17:53,540
All right. Have a good time with Dad.

289
00:17:54,850 --> 00:17:56,810
(Lawyer Kang Baek Ho)

290
00:17:56,880 --> 00:17:58,850
(Law Firm Leeho)

291
00:18:13,560 --> 00:18:17,070
Why isn't Baek Ho here yet?
He should have been here ages ago.

292
00:18:17,570 --> 00:18:20,640
I even picked a place
right near his office.

293
00:18:21,170 --> 00:18:22,540
Maybe he's not coming?

294
00:18:22,740 --> 00:18:24,940
Come on, he wouldn't dare.

295
00:18:31,380 --> 00:18:32,380
It's so bitter.

296
00:18:34,590 --> 00:18:37,050
Did he actually stand me up?

297
00:18:39,860 --> 00:18:40,960
Welcome.

298
00:18:42,390 --> 00:18:43,430
She's over there.

299
00:18:48,330 --> 00:18:49,470
Jin Hong Ju.

300
00:18:50,070 --> 00:18:51,200
Jin Hong Ju.

301
00:18:52,400 --> 00:18:54,470
Why have you had so much to drink?

302
00:18:56,210 --> 00:18:57,540
Baek Ho.

303
00:18:57,540 --> 00:18:59,040
Are you with me?

304
00:18:59,580 --> 00:19:01,850
Let's get you home.
You can make it home, can't you?

305
00:19:01,980 --> 00:19:04,820
Are we going for round two?

306
00:19:06,320 --> 00:19:08,650
Come on, get up.

307
00:19:08,990 --> 00:19:10,020
Come on.

308
00:19:21,200 --> 00:19:22,270
Are you okay?

309
00:19:28,040 --> 00:19:29,440
I'm totally fine.

310
00:19:29,910 --> 00:19:32,840
Then why did you drink so much
if you can't hold your liquor?

311
00:19:33,240 --> 00:19:35,580
It's because
you weren't answering my calls.

312
00:19:35,980 --> 00:19:38,820
I was waiting for you,
so I had a drink, and then another...

313
00:19:40,220 --> 00:19:42,790
- Let's have just one more for the road.
- Oh, no...

314
00:19:43,390 --> 00:19:44,560
Let's get you home.

315
00:19:44,890 --> 00:19:49,460
- I'll take you home.
- Baek Ho, come on. Just one more.

316
00:19:50,390 --> 00:19:52,500
You're already so drunk.
Why would you want another one?

317
00:19:52,800 --> 00:19:54,330
If you keep this up,
I'm just going to leave you here.

318
00:19:55,270 --> 00:19:56,870
Baek Ho, you're so mean.

319
00:19:59,170 --> 00:20:01,570
I'm dizzy. My legs feel like jelly.

320
00:20:02,070 --> 00:20:04,610
Brace your legs. Seriously...

321
00:20:05,880 --> 00:20:06,880
Unbelievable.

322
00:20:07,580 --> 00:20:09,810
Darn it.

323
00:20:33,500 --> 00:20:35,070
Come on, up you go.

324
00:20:35,740 --> 00:20:37,840
- Baek Ho.
- Come on.

325
00:20:39,380 --> 00:20:40,480
Let's go home. Come on.

326
00:20:41,880 --> 00:20:43,810
Try to walk properly, will you?

327
00:20:54,860 --> 00:20:56,390
When did those two...

328
00:20:57,190 --> 00:20:58,530
get so close?

329
00:21:01,030 --> 00:21:02,070
Baek Ho.

330
00:21:02,970 --> 00:21:05,840
Have you completely forgotten
about me now?

331
00:21:07,070 --> 00:21:08,210
You haven't, right?

332
00:21:09,710 --> 00:21:11,840
No. It can't be.

333
00:21:16,150 --> 00:21:17,280
I swear, I can't believe this.

334
00:21:17,580 --> 00:21:18,780
Baek Ho.

335
00:21:19,620 --> 00:21:23,390
- Oh my goodness, what happened?
- Baek Ho.

336
00:21:24,220 --> 00:21:26,260
Hey! Get ahold of yourself.

337
00:21:26,320 --> 00:21:27,990
It looks like your daughter
had a little too much to drink.

338
00:21:30,990 --> 00:21:35,130
Why would you let her drink so much?
She's a lightweight.

339
00:21:35,470 --> 00:21:38,340
- You should've cut her off.
- I wasn't the one who got her drunk.

340
00:21:38,400 --> 00:21:39,940
And who are you?

341
00:21:40,540 --> 00:21:42,240
Are you dating Hong Ju?

342
00:21:42,570 --> 00:21:46,810
I'm Kang Baek Ho.
I am absolutely not dating Hong Ju.

343
00:21:47,440 --> 00:21:50,510
Baek Ho, I had so much fun tonight.

344
00:21:50,910 --> 00:21:52,720
Let's have a drink right here.

345
00:21:53,120 --> 00:21:56,220
Not dating, my foot.
I told her again and again to stop,

346
00:21:56,220 --> 00:21:58,590
but she wouldn't listen and met him again.

347
00:21:58,960 --> 00:22:01,090
Just get her upstairs, will you?

348
00:22:02,060 --> 00:22:05,560
- Hurry up. This is so upsetting.
- Baek Ho.

349
00:22:07,660 --> 00:22:09,800
- Over there.
- Okay.

350
00:22:10,170 --> 00:22:12,270
Please try to walk straight.

351
00:22:13,340 --> 00:22:15,570
- Here we go.
- Oh my.

352
00:22:16,140 --> 00:22:17,770
Baek Ho.

353
00:22:19,940 --> 00:22:21,080
Well, I should be going now.

354
00:22:21,680 --> 00:22:22,780
Baek Ho.

355
00:22:23,480 --> 00:22:25,550
Thank you so much.

356
00:22:26,180 --> 00:22:28,590
- Let's get a cup of tea.
- Jin Hong Ju.

357
00:22:29,120 --> 00:22:31,150
Pull yourself together
and don't do this again.

358
00:22:31,560 --> 00:22:33,160
And let me make myself clear
one more time.

359
00:22:33,760 --> 00:22:35,990
We are absolutely not dating,
so please don't get the wrong idea.

360
00:22:38,100 --> 00:22:39,100
Baek Ho.

361
00:22:42,900 --> 00:22:46,140
What was he talking about?
What did he mean, you two are not dating?

362
00:22:47,140 --> 00:22:49,640
So you've just been pathetically pining
for him this whole time?

363
00:22:49,770 --> 00:22:51,440
- Mom.
- You scared me!

364
00:22:51,880 --> 00:22:56,310
I swear, I can't with you, Mom.
You ruined everything!

365
00:22:57,450 --> 00:23:00,620
What are you talking about?
Were you faking it this whole time?

366
00:23:01,890 --> 00:23:04,320
Oh, please. "I can't with you, Mom?"

367
00:23:04,320 --> 00:23:05,660
I'm the one who can't stand you!

368
00:23:05,720 --> 00:23:07,020
- Seriously.
- It hurts.

369
00:23:07,120 --> 00:23:08,530
Have you no shame?

370
00:23:09,730 --> 00:23:10,730
Unbelievable.

371
00:23:55,710 --> 00:23:57,070
Lawyer Kang Baek Ho?

372
00:23:58,240 --> 00:23:59,380
What brings you here?

373
00:23:59,710 --> 00:24:00,980
Jang Mi, it's me.

374
00:24:02,110 --> 00:24:03,150
Kang Baek Ho.

375
00:24:05,950 --> 00:24:07,750
I don't know what you're talking about.

376
00:24:08,320 --> 00:24:09,350
Wait.

377
00:24:11,250 --> 00:24:12,260
Wait.

378
00:24:14,160 --> 00:24:15,590
Are you Director Ma Seo Rin?

379
00:24:19,600 --> 00:24:20,600
Yes.

380
00:24:23,500 --> 00:24:25,770
But you and Jang Mi look so alike.
You could be twins.

381
00:24:27,100 --> 00:24:28,340
Are you...

382
00:24:28,340 --> 00:24:29,670
I'm sorry, Baek Ho.

383
00:24:30,770 --> 00:24:31,780
I'm so sorry.

384
00:24:33,140 --> 00:24:34,380
What do you mean, twins?

385
00:24:35,050 --> 00:24:36,380
That's such a ridiculous thing to say...

386
00:24:42,390 --> 00:24:43,620
But I know it's you, Jang Mi.

387
00:24:45,190 --> 00:24:46,560
You can't fool me.

388
00:24:47,660 --> 00:24:49,460
Your expression
and the look in your eyes...

389
00:24:50,190 --> 00:24:51,390
You think I wouldn't know?

390
00:24:57,500 --> 00:24:58,700
What happened?

391
00:25:00,900 --> 00:25:02,370
Jang Mi, why are you...

392
00:25:03,270 --> 00:25:04,510
Why are you here?

393
00:25:09,380 --> 00:25:10,380
Jang Mi.

394
00:25:13,150 --> 00:25:14,150
Baek Ho.

395
00:25:21,830 --> 00:25:22,830
I'm sorry.

396
00:25:24,490 --> 00:25:25,500
I'm so sorry.

397
00:25:28,160 --> 00:25:29,170
Jang Mi.

398
00:25:29,700 --> 00:25:31,170
When did you wake up?

399
00:25:31,940 --> 00:25:33,540
And how did you end up here?

400
00:25:35,070 --> 00:25:36,640
Are you feeling okay?

401
00:25:37,870 --> 00:25:39,310
Your face was injured so badly.

402
00:25:40,180 --> 00:25:41,340
What happened?

403
00:25:44,180 --> 00:25:45,350
Baek Ho.

404
00:25:45,550 --> 00:25:48,650
We should go talk in your car.

405
00:25:59,960 --> 00:26:02,630
Let's just go, Baek Ho. We'll talk later.

406
00:26:02,870 --> 00:26:06,840
- I don't understand any of this.
- Someone might see us. Let's go, quickly.

407
00:26:08,910 --> 00:26:09,910
Okay.

408
00:26:17,180 --> 00:26:19,180
(Law Firm Leeho)

409
00:26:24,990 --> 00:26:26,960
(Lawyer Kang Baek Ho)

410
00:26:40,040 --> 00:26:41,500
I hope this isn't a dream.

411
00:26:44,010 --> 00:26:45,310
This really isn't a dream, is it?

412
00:26:47,780 --> 00:26:49,510
It's not a dream, Baek Ho.

413
00:26:54,680 --> 00:26:56,090
It's really you, isn't it, Jang Mi?

414
00:26:57,920 --> 00:26:59,190
I can't believe it.

415
00:27:00,190 --> 00:27:01,320
I still can't believe it.

416
00:27:02,430 --> 00:27:03,490
You can believe it.

417
00:27:04,560 --> 00:27:05,900
It's me. It's Jang Mi.

418
00:27:06,900 --> 00:27:09,670
I'm the same Oh Jang Mi who loves you.

419
00:27:12,400 --> 00:27:13,600
Thank you, Jang Mi.

420
00:27:15,640 --> 00:27:17,210
Thank you so much, Jang Mi.

421
00:27:57,050 --> 00:27:58,580
(The First Man)

422
00:27:58,680 --> 00:28:00,850
Chae Hwa Young was behind all of it.

423
00:28:00,950 --> 00:28:02,690
Footage of her
directly harming your father...

424
00:28:02,690 --> 00:28:04,090
would be the smoking gun.

425
00:28:04,090 --> 00:28:05,890
We have to find it, no matter what.

426
00:28:05,960 --> 00:28:08,220
I don't have feelings for
General Director Kang Jun Ho anymore.

427
00:28:08,290 --> 00:28:10,360
Why are you suddenly acting
like a completely different person?

428
00:28:10,430 --> 00:28:13,460
People change. Did you expect me
to stay devoted to him forever?

429
00:28:13,660 --> 00:28:17,000
Chae Hwa Young is a monster.
I can never forgive her.

430
00:28:17,130 --> 00:28:20,400
I think CEO Chae is being blackmailed.

431
00:28:23,440 --> 00:28:25,440
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
